                <div class="headline">
                    <h2>Domain Name FAQs</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-group acc-v1 margin-bottom-30" id="accordion">

                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseDomainPointing" id="DomainPointing">
                                    Can I point my domain name to WIX or Shopify or another website builder?
                                </a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseDomainPointing" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>Yes. We even have dedicated support articles for the popular options and our support team can assist you if you need any help.</p>
                                <p><strong>Wix</strong></p>
                                <p><strong>Shopify</strong> - <a href="https://www.nuttyabouthosting.co.uk/knowledgebase/article/setup-shopify" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">How to point your domain name</a></p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseEmailForwarding" id="EmailForwarding">
                                    What are email forwarders?
                                </a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseEmailForwarding" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>We provide you with 5 email forwarders with your domain name, 4 standard forwarders and 1 group forwarder (with 3 recipients).</p>
                                <p>Our standard forwarders allow you to create an email addresses like hello&commat; and forward all the emails automatically to, for example, your-name@gmail.com</p>
                                <p>Our group forwarder allows you to create an email addresses like hello&commat; and forward all the emails automatically to multiple email address, for example, your-name@gmail.com, your-business-partner@gmail.com and your-accountant@their-domain-name.co.uk</p>
                                <p>
                                    You can not send emails using your domain name with email forwarders. You will need to either purchase a <a href="/email">dedicated email package</a> or a <a href="/hosting">web hosting package</a> which comes with email hosting too.
                                </p>
                                <p>You can also use these forwarders to be RFC compliant with postmaster&commat;, abuse&commat; & webmaster&commat;</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseEmailHosting" id="EmailHosting">
                                    Can I send email using my domain name?
                                </a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseEmailHosting" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>If you want to send email using your domain name then you will need email hosting.</p>
                                <p>This costs just 99p per month per email address and you get large 2GB mailboxes, spam and virus protection and our great support. Read more about our <a href="/email">email hosting</a> or <a href="/hosting">web hosting package</a> which comes with email hosting too.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseWebsiteForwarding" id="WebsiteForwarding">
                                    Do you do website forwarding?
                                </a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseWebsiteForwarding" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>
                                    Yes, when you have transferred in your domain name you can set up web forwarding by following this article on <a href="/knowledgebase/article/how-to-set-up-web-forwarding">How to set up Web Forwarding</a>.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseNominet" id="Nominet">
                                    Who are Nominet?
                                </a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseNominet" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>Nominet are the official registry responsible for .UK domain names. This includes .uk, .co.uk, .org.uk and others. We work closely with Nominet and have achieved their highest accredited partner status. Being a Nominet Accredited Channel Partner means we have strict business processes in place to provide customers with the best service possible. These are audited every year by Nominet.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseNonUKResident" id="NonUKResident">
                                    I don't live in the UK, can I still buy a UK domain name?
                                </a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseNonUKResident" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>Anyone can purchase either a .co.uk or a .org.uk or a .me.uk</p>
                                <p>If you are purchasing a .uk and don't have UK address we would become the admin contact on your behalf. You would still be the registrant and the domain name would belong to you.</p>
                                <p>To purchase a .ltd.uk domain name you must be a UK limited company.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseWHOISOptOut" id="WHOISOptOut">
                                    Can I hide my details from the WHOIS database?
                                </a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseWHOISOptOut" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>Since GDPR all details are now hidden from public view regardless of the registrant type.</p>
                                <p>If you wish your details to be made public then please <a href="/contact">contact us</a> after you have purchasd your domain name.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseDNS" id="DNS">
                                    What is DNS?
                                </a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseDNS" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>DNS or Domain Name System controls your domain name's email and website settings.</p>
                                <p>When someone visits or sends an email to your domain name the DNS settings are responsible for telling the visitors computer where those items are. For example www on our domain name nuttyabouthosting.co.uk points to the IP address 188.65.176.76 which is on our servers.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <h4 class="panel-title">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseDNSNameserverDifferences" id="DNSNameserverDifferences">
                                    What is the difference between DNS and nameservers?
                                </a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseDNSNameserverDifferences" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>A nameserver is a server on the internet that holds the DNS for a domain name.</p>
                                <p>The nameservers for a domain name are held at the registry for that domains tld i.e. Nominet (.uk domains etc) or ICANN (.com domains etc). Any request for a domain is then forwarded to these nameservers (i.e. ns1.nuttyabouthosting.co.uk) and they let the requesting query know where that resource is i.e. an IP address.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div><!--/acc-v1-->
                <!-- End FAQ -->
            </div>
        </div>

